{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a sequence of pairs ("},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}]},{"type":"text","text":"), where "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}]},{"type":"text","text":" represents a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consecutive integer starting at zero and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}]},{"type":"text","text":" represents an element of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the sequence."}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"role":"symbol","extendedModule":"Swift","externalID":"s:STsE10enumerateds18EnumeratedSequenceVyxGyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:s13KeyValuePairsV","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"title":"enumerated()"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/swift/keyvaluepairs/enumerated()"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/KeyValuePairs/enumerated()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence","preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV","text":"EnumeratedSequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A sequence of pairs enumerating the sequence."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example enumerates the characters of the string “Swift” and prints"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each character along with its place in the string."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["for (n, c) in \"Swift\".enumerated() {","    print(\"\\(n): '\\(c)'\")","}","// Prints \"0: 'S'\"","// Prints \"1: 'w'\"","// Prints \"2: 'i'\"","// Prints \"3: 'f'\"","// Prints \"4: 't'\""],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you enumerate a collection, the integer part of each pair is a counter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the enumeration, but is not necessarily the index of the paired value."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These counters can be used as indices only in instances of zero-based,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integer-indexed collections, such as "},{"code":"Array","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"ContiguousArray","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other collections the counters may be out of range or of the wrong type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to use as an index. To iterate over the elements of a collection with its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"indices, use the "},{"code":"zip(_:_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example iterates over the indices and elements of a set, building a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"list consisting of indices of names with five or fewer letters."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let names: Set = [\"Sofia\", \"Camilla\", \"Martina\", \"Mateo\", \"Nicolás\"]","var shorterIndices: [Set<String>.Index] = []","for (i, name) in zip(names.indices, names) {","    if name.count <= 5 {","        shorterIndices.append(i)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that the "},{"code":"shorterIndices","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" array holds the indices of the shorter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"names in the "},{"code":"names","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" set, you can use those indices to access elements in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the set."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["for i in shorterIndices {","    print(names[i])","}","// Prints \"Sofia\"","// Prints \"Mateo\""],"syntax":"swift"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"O(1)"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Complexity","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/KeyValuePairs"]]},"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","type":"topic","url":"/documentation/swift","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Build apps using a powerful open language.","type":"text"}],"title":"Swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence":{"url":"/documentation/swift/enumeratedsequence","title":"EnumeratedSequence","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An enumeration of the elements of a sequence or collection."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EnumeratedSequence","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence","kind":"symbol"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/KeyValuePairs/enumerated()":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV","text":"EnumeratedSequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"role":"symbol","url":"/documentation/swift/keyvaluepairs/enumerated()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a sequence of pairs ("},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}]},{"type":"text","text":"), where "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}]},{"type":"text","text":" represents a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consecutive integer starting at zero and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}]},{"type":"text","text":" represents an element of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the sequence."}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/KeyValuePairs/enumerated()","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"enumerated()"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/KeyValuePairs":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"KeyValuePairs"}],"url":"/documentation/swift/keyvaluepairs","title":"KeyValuePairs","abstract":[{"text":"A lightweight collection of key-value pairs.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"KeyValuePairs"}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/KeyValuePairs","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"}}}